---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'About WattLibrary';
const description = 'WattLibrary is an independent portable power station database: how we collect specs and estimate runtimes.';
---
<Base {title} {description}>
  <h1>About WattLibrary</h1>
  <p style="max-width:640px;">
    WattLibrary started with a simple frustration: power station spec sheets are scattered, inconsistent, and sometimes
    misleading. We collect the numbers into one structured database and present them the same way for every model, so
    comparisons are fair.
  </p>
  <h2>How we work</h2>
  <p style="max-width:640px;">
    Specifications come from manufacturer documentation and manuals; each listing links to its source. Runtime estimates use a
    transparent formula (capacity × 85% inverter efficiency ÷ appliance draw) — we show the assumptions, not just the result.
    When we're not sure about a number, we don't publish it.
  </p>
  <h2>Independence</h2>
  <p style="max-width:640px;">
    WattLibrary currently runs no ads and contains no affiliate links. No brand pays to be listed, and no brand can pay to
    change its numbers. If that ever changes, we'll disclose it clearly on every affected page.
  </p>
  <h2>Corrections</h2>
  <p style="max-width:640px;">
    Spotted an error? Email us and we'll verify and correct it within 24 hours: hello@wattlibrary.com
  </p>
</Base>
